X = np.zeros((int(data.shape[0]), img_ht, img_wt, 3))
Y = np.zeros((int(data.shape[0]), img_ht, img_wt))      
for index in range(data.shape[0]):
    img = data[index][0]
    img = cv2.resize(img, dsize = (img_ht, img_wt), interpolation = cv2.INTER_CUBIC)
    try:
      img = img[:, :, :3]
    except:
      continue
    X[index] = preprocess_input(np.array(img, dtype = np.float32))
    for i in data[index][1]:
        x1 = int(i['points'][0]['x'] * img_wt)
        x2 = int(i['points'][1]['x'] * img_wt)
        y1 = int(i['points'][0]['y'] * img_ht)
        y2 = int(i['points'][1]['y'] * img_ht)
        Y[index][y1:y2, x1:x2] = 1

ALPHA = 1
HEIGHT_CELLS = 28
WIDTH_CELLS = 28
In [24]:
def create_model(trainable=True):
    model = MobileNet(input_shape=(img_ht, img_wt, 3), include_top=False, alpha=ALPHA, weights="imagenet")

    for layer in model.layers:
        layer.trainable = trainable

    block1 = model.get_layer("conv_pw_5_relu").output
    block2 = model.get_layer("conv_pw_11_relu").output
    block3 = model.get_layer("conv_pw_13_relu").output

    x = Concatenate()([UpSampling2D()(block3), block2])
    x = Concatenate()([UpSampling2D()(x), block1])

    x = Conv2D(1, kernel_size=1, activation="sigmoid")(x)
    x = Reshape((HEIGHT_CELLS, WIDTH_CELLS))(x)

    return Model(inputs=model.input, outputs=x)

# Q2 B
In [27]:
# Dice coefficient
In [28]:
def dice_coef(y_true, y_pred):
    numerator = 2 * tensorflow.reduce_sum(y_true * y_pred)
    denominator = tensorflow.reduce_sum(y_true + y_pred)

    return numerator / (denominator + tensorflow.keras.backend.epsilon())
In [29]:
# Loss function
In [30]:
def loss(y_true, y_pred):
    return binary_crossentropy(y_true, y_pred) - tensorflow.keras.backend.log(dice_coefficient(y_true, y_pred) + tensorflow.keras.backend.epsilon())

# Q2 - Write a loop which will iterate through all the images in the training_images folder and detect the faces present on all the images.
In [40]:
trained_face_data = cv2.CascadeClassifier(cv2.data.haarcascades+'haarcascade_frontalface_default.xml')
In [41]:
def detect_faces(image):
    gray_img = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)
    face_coordinates = trained_face_data.detectMultiScale(gray_img)
    face_data = []
    
    for coordinate in face_coordinates:
        (x, y, w, h) = coordinate
        face_data.append([x, y, w, h])
        
        colors = np.random.randint(1, 255, 3)
        cv2.rectangle(image, (x, y), (x+w, y+h), (int(colors[0]), int(colors[1]), int(colors[2])), thickness=2)
    
    return face_data, image
In [42]:
columns = ['Image_Path', 'x', 'y', 'width', 'height']

In [43]:
for filename in os.listdir(folder_path):
    if filename.endswith('.jpg'):
        image_path = os.path.join(folder_path, filename)
        image = cv2.imread(image_path)
        face_data, modified_image = detect_faces(image)
        temp_df = pd.DataFrame(face_data, columns=['x', 'y', 'width', 'height'])
        temp_df['Image_Path'] = filename
        temp_df['Num_Faces'] = len(face_data)
        df_metadata = pd.concat([df_metadata, temp_df], ignore_index=True)
cv2.destroyAllWindows()

# Q2 - Write function to create metadata of the image
In [56]:
class IdentityMetadata():
    def __init__(self, base, name, file):
        self.base = base
        self.name = name
        self.file = file
    def __repr__(self):
        return self.image_path()
    def image_path(self):
        return os.path.join(self.base, self.name, self.file)
In [58]:
def load_metadata(path):
    metadata = []
    for i in os.listdir(path):
        for f in os.listdir(os.path.join(path, i)):
            ext = os.path.splitext(f)[1]
            if ext == '.jpg' or ext == '.jpeg':
                metadata.append(IdentityMetadata(path, i, f))
    return np.array(metadata)

def load_image(path):
    img = cv2.imread(path, 1)
    return img[...,::-1]

# Q4 - Generate Embeddings vectors on the each face in the dataset
In [68]:
def vgg_face():
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1),input_shape=(224,224, 3)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(MaxPooling2D((2,2), strides=(2,2)))
    
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(128, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(128, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(MaxPooling2D((2,2), strides=(2,2)))
    
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(256, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(256, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(256, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(MaxPooling2D((2,2), strides=(2,2)))
    
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(512, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(512, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(512, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(MaxPooling2D((2,2), strides=(2,2)))
    
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(512, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(512, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(512, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(MaxPooling2D((2,2), strides=(2,2)))
    
    model.add(Convolution2D(4096, (7, 7), activation='relu'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.5))
    model.add(Convolution2D(4096, (1, 1), activation='relu'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.5))
    model.add(Convolution2D(2622, (1, 1)))
    model.add(Flatten())
    model.add(Activation('softmax'))
    return model

embeddings = np.zeros((metadata.shape[0], 2622))

for i, m in enumerate(metadata):
    img_path = metadata[i].image_path()
    img = load_image(img_path)
    img = (img / 255.).astype(np.float32)
    img = cv2.resize(img, dsize = (224,224))
    embedding_vector = vgg_face_descriptor.predict(np.expand_dims(img, axis=0))[0]
    embeddings[i]=embedding_vector

# Q5 - Build distance metrics for identifying the distance between two similar and dissimilar images
In [74]:
def distance(emb1, emb2):
    return np.sum(np.square(emb1 - emb2))
In [75]:
def show_pair(idx1, idx2):
    plt.figure(figsize=(8,3))
    plt.suptitle(f'Distance = {distance(embeddings[idx1], embeddings[idx2]):.2f}')
    plt.subplot(121)
    plt.imshow(load_image(metadata[idx1].image_path()))
    plt.subplot(122)
    plt.imshow(load_image(metadata[idx2].image_path()));
In [76]:

show_pair(2, 180)

# Q6 - Use PCA for dimensionality reduction
In [81]:
train_idx = np.arange(metadata.shape[0]) % 9 != 0
test_idx = np.arange(metadata.shape[0]) % 9 == 0
X_train = embeddings[train_idx]
X_test = embeddings[test_idx]
targets = np.array([m.name for m in metadata])
y_train = targets[train_idx]
y_test = targets[test_idx]
In [82]:
# Encoding
In [83]:
LE = LabelEncoder()
y_train = LE.fit_transform(y_train)
y_test = LE.transform(y_test)
In [84]:
# Standardization
In [85]:
std = StandardScaler()
X_train_s = std.fit_transform(X_train)
X_test_s = std.transform(X_test)
In [86]:
pca = PCA(n_components = 128)
X_train_pca = pca.fit_transform(X_train_s)
X_test_pca = pca.transform(X_test_s)
In [87]:
# Q7 - Build an SVM classifier in order to map each image to its right person

clf.fit(X_train_pca, y_train)
